Advance Musoki was arrested and charged with being a criminal nuisance. HARARE - A student in Zimbabwe is in court today after he staged a demonstration against President Robert Mugabe during a graduation ceremony last week. The student was arrested and charged with being a criminal nuisance. Advance Musoki spent a night in custody last week, before being released on free bail at the weekend. He s now due in court in the second city of Bulawayo. Musoki was arrested and charged with criminal nuisance after he stood up during a graduation ceremony on Friday and shouted We want jobs&quot; in Shona.President Mugabe, who is chancellor of all state universities, was at Bulawayo s National University of Science and Technology to cap hundreds of graduates. In September, a student was arrested for standing up with a placard to demand jobs during graduation at the main University of Zimbabwe in Harare.